"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"The launch of a Bitcoin ETF played a pivotal role in the rise of BTC adoption.\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/tyiPcJeYdlp1gzzEY-gzA.png?height=782&width=1174)\\n\\nAccording to a report [published](https://grayscale.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Grayscale-2021-Bitcoin-Investor-Study.pdf) by Grayscale Investments on Monday, more than one-quarter of U.S. investors surveyed (26%) said they already own Bitcoin ([BTC](https://cointelegraph.com/bitcoin-price)). Out of this group of owners, 46% and 44% also jointly held Ethereum ([ETH](https://cointelegraph.com/ethereum-price)) and Dogecoin ([DOGE](https://cointelegraph.com/doge-price-index)) in their accounts, respectively. An additional three-quarters of the participants (77%) said they would likely [gain exposure to Bitcoin through an exchange-traded fund](https://cointelegraph.com/news/cointelegraph-consulting-etfs-listed-what-s-next-for-bitcoin).\\n\\nThe survey featured 1,000 respondents between the ages of 25 and 64. All had at least $10,000 in investable household assets (excluding workplace retirement plans or real estate) and at least $50,000 in household income. Most invest in cryptocurrencies via a trading app or directly through a crypto exchange. Very few invest in Bitcoin through a traditional self-brokerage or industry professionals. In fact, the number of respondents using a financial advisor for crypto exposure fell from 30% in 2020 to just 11% this year.\\n\\nIn terms of investment planning, three times as many investors would consider owning BTC as an investment rather than a currency. Furthermore, over 50% of participants said they perceive Bitcoin as a long-term play that can fit in their overall portfolio strategy. Seventy-seven percent said they had purchased BTC within the last 12 months. Ninety-one percent of respondents are currently in the green regarding their investment.\\n\\nThere were near-universal increases in Bitcoin adoption across all age groups, genders and levels of education. The reported cited being able to invest very low amounts, accessibility at any time and a large sector growth potential as [key reasons for its popularity](https://cointelegraph.com/news/bitcoin-whales-move-fresh-coins-to-exchanges-in-repeat-of-behavior-before-42k-btc-price-dip).\",\"timestamp\":1639482301,\"title\":\"Grayscale finds that over 25% of US households surveyed currently own Bitcoin\"},\"digest\":\"PK-_D54Mi0pCZ9SWYgW8dIlELEgJAZWZJL2NUOG1LwA\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x6fc8a8e314Ab3244E3ED43FEc646B54a0A94249e\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"kwskuyI4xBplHMrxwxeqXYkTD8ObFRUHR7UpO-4fNo8\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"mqXM1ua5zM8QZ2GTbjRXNyHc98mQb4V1zVQ0tU-EGZc\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"d-33zVZBLSGIUWihEV_CNSOoYpNrAVOoAPSNzw2yXjRZA7FbpB8kY36YToO1IDht4SM-PbQyrfgTXMYlR_poeA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xe5026c9aee3d0340b0ff1d4103e7e4231c7f2137b26c275efe356fd8dca7133306989957396b93ab69a8d995f0031ffa4595600ababc7f65c4b228fb87b40a2d1b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"kwskuyI4xBplHMrxwxeqXYkTD8ObFRUHR7UpO-4fNo8\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"mqXM1ua5zM8QZ2GTbjRXNyHc98mQb4V1zVQ0tU-EGZc\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"PK-_D54Mi0pCZ9SWYgW8dIlELEgJAZWZJL2NUOG1LwA\"}"